      <title>How to Use Flow Mode for Grafana Agent (Grafana Office Hours #21)</title>
      <link>https://nicolevanderhoeven.github.io/blog/20231124-goh21-how-to-use-flow-mode-for-grafana-agent/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 24 Nov 2023 11:47:00 +0100</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://nicolevanderhoeven.github.io/blog/20231124-goh21-how-to-use-flow-mode-for-grafana-agent/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Senior Software Engineer Matt Durham shows us how to use flow mode for Grafana Agent. Flow mode is a new and better way to install and configure Grafana Agent than the older &amp;ldquo;static mode&amp;rdquo;. Among other things, flow mode&amp;rsquo;s modularity makes it easier to build more complex workflows like traditional data pipelines and allows for more use cases than collecting and processing telemetry.&lt;/p&gt;

